### Revised Proof

```lean
@[sorryful]
lemma quadSolsInclLinSols_injective (χ : ACCSystemQuad) :
    Function.Injective χ.quadSolsInclLinSols := by
  intro s t h
  have h₁ : s.val = t.val := by
    ext i
    have h₂ := h
    simp [QuadSols.ext_iff] at h₂
    <;> simp_all [Subtype.val_mk]
    <;> aesop
  exact Subtype.ext h₁
```

This proof uses the fact that two `QuadSols` objects are equal if their underlying charges (`val`) are equal. It leverages the `ext` tactic to compare the values of the charges at each index `i` and then uses the injectivity of the inclusion map to conclude that the original objects are equal. The proof avoids unnecessary complexity by directly comparing the charges and using subtype properties.
